public class RaycastError : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Update()
    {
        // Forgot to check if hit collider is null!
        RaycastHit2D hit = Physics2D.Raycast(transform.position, Vector2.right, 10f);
        Debug.Log(hit.collider.gameObject.name);  // NullReferenceException!
    }
}

phase2.explanation:
You're trying to access a collider that doesn't exist because the ray didn't hit anything.

**The fix:**
```csharp
RaycastHit2D hit = Physics2D.Raycast(transform.position, Vector2.right, 10f);
if (hit.collider != null)
{
    Debug.Log(hit.collider.gameObject.name);
}
```

**Sharp-chan says:**
"Always check if the ray hit something before using the result."
